{"type": "text", "stream": "stdout", "text": "Looking at the STATE.md, I can see the core issue. The current parser expects the MAC address as exactly 12 hex chars with no colons (the format observed from random-address phones in privacy mode). The Samsung SmartTag `00:A0:50:F0:35:4B` is a **public address** device — the FC41D might emit it in a different format (17-char colon format, or using the manual's field order where `addr` is first, not RSSI).", "ts": "2026-05-17T20:57:55+00:00", "time": "23:57:55"}
{"type": "text", "stream": "stdout", "text": "I'll fix `parse_qblescan` to:", "ts": "2026-05-17T20:57:55+00:00", "time": "23:57:55"}
{"type": "text", "stream": "stdout", "text": "1. Auto-detect field order (RSSI-first vs addr-first)", "ts": "2026-05-17T20:57:55+00:00", "time": "23:57:55"}
{"type": "text", "stream": "stdout", "text": "2. Accept both 12-char no-colon and 17-char colon MAC formats", "ts": "2026-05-17T20:57:55+00:00", "time": "23:57:55"}
{"type": "text", "stream": "stdout", "text": "3. Add `[PARSE-FAIL]` trace so we can see exactly what's being rejected", "ts": "2026-05-17T20:57:55+00:00", "time": "23:57:55"}
