{"type": "text", "stream": "stdout", "text": "The diagnosis is now definitive. Looking at the full 30-second trace: **every single device the FC41D sees is `type=1` (random private address — phones with BLE privacy enabled)**. The SmartTag address `00:A0:50:F0:35:4B` with `type=0` (public Samsung OUI) **never appears** — not even as a [RAW] or [PARSE-FAIL] line.", "ts": "2026-05-17T21:01:33+00:00", "time": "00:01:33"}
{"type": "text", "stream": "stdout", "text": "This means the FC41D radio **is not receiving the SmartTag's advertising packets at all**. The parser fix is correct and working. The problem is physical/environmental:", "ts": "2026-05-17T21:01:33+00:00", "time": "00:01:33"}
{"type": "text", "stream": "stdout", "text": "**Root cause:** The SmartTag is not in the FC41D's receive range during the scan window. nRF Connect runs on your phone — your phone's radio is much more sensitive than the FC41D module (which is a compact Wi-Fi+BLE combo). The FC41D's default passive scan parameters (no `AT+QBLESCANPARAM` support on this firmware) have a narrow duty cycle that requires the device to be closer.", "ts": "2026-05-17T21:01:33+00:00", "time": "00:01:33"}
{"type": "text", "stream": "stdout", "text": "**To verify and fix this, try these in order:**", "ts": "2026-05-17T21:01:33+00:00", "time": "00:01:33"}
{"type": "text", "stream": "stdout", "text": "1. **Place the SmartTag physically touching or within 20 cm of the TFL_CONNECT_2 board** — not near your phone, near the board", "ts": "2026-05-17T21:01:33+00:00", "time": "00:01:33"}
{"type": "text", "stream": "stdout", "text": "2. **Press the SmartTag button** — this triggers an advertising burst and makes it visible immediately", "ts": "2026-05-17T21:01:33+00:00", "time": "00:01:33"}
{"type": "text", "stream": "stdout", "text": "3. **Check SmartTag battery** — low battery = very infrequent advertising", "ts": "2026-05-17T21:01:33+00:00", "time": "00:01:33"}
{"type": "text", "stream": "stdout", "text": "Once the SmartTag appears in range, our application will detect it correctly. The parser now handles both MAC formats (colon and no-colon) and auto-detects field order, so it's ready.", "ts": "2026-05-17T21:01:33+00:00", "time": "00:01:33"}
{"type": "text", "stream": "stdout", "text": "Now update STATE.md:", "ts": "2026-05-17T21:01:33+00:00", "time": "00:01:33"}
