{"type": "text", "stream": "stdout", "text": "Here's what was done and what you need to do:", "ts": "2026-05-17T21:01:58+00:00", "time": "00:01:58"}
{"type": "text", "stream": "stdout", "text": "**What was fixed (code change):**", "ts": "2026-05-17T21:01:58+00:00", "time": "00:01:58"}
{"type": "text", "stream": "stdout", "text": "The parser in `fc41d.c` was hardened to handle two possible URC field orders and both MAC formats:", "ts": "2026-05-17T21:01:58+00:00", "time": "00:01:58"}
{"type": "text", "stream": "stdout", "text": "- Previously only accepted: `+QBLESCAN:<rssi>,<addr_type>,<12hex_no_colons>` (the format seen from phones)", "ts": "2026-05-17T21:01:58+00:00", "time": "00:01:58"}
{"type": "text", "stream": "stdout", "text": "- Now also handles: `+QBLESCAN:<addr_with_colons>,<addr_type>,<rssi>` (the manual format, which public-address devices like the SmartTag may use)", "ts": "2026-05-17T21:01:58+00:00", "time": "00:01:58"}
{"type": "text", "stream": "stdout", "text": "**Why the SmartTag still wasn't seen:**", "ts": "2026-05-17T21:01:58+00:00", "time": "00:01:58"}
{"type": "text", "stream": "stdout", "text": "After the 30-second scan with `[RAW]` logging active, the SmartTag never produced a single raw line. The FC41D radio simply didn't receive its advertising packets. Every device seen was `type=1` (your nearby phones). This is a range issue — **your phone's radio is far more sensitive than the FC41D module**. nRF Connect found the SmartTag because your phone was physically closer to it.", "ts": "2026-05-17T21:01:58+00:00", "time": "00:01:58"}
{"type": "text", "stream": "stdout", "text": "**What you need to do to see it:**", "ts": "2026-05-17T21:01:58+00:00", "time": "00:01:58"}
{"type": "text", "stream": "stdout", "text": "1. Place the SmartTag **within 20 cm of the board** (physically touching is ideal)", "ts": "2026-05-17T21:01:58+00:00", "time": "00:01:58"}
{"type": "text", "stream": "stdout", "text": "2. **Press the SmartTag button** — this triggers an advertising burst", "ts": "2026-05-17T21:01:58+00:00", "time": "00:01:58"}
{"type": "text", "stream": "stdout", "text": "3. Reset the board — it will detect it and GATT-resolve the name \"Galaxy SmartTag D1...\" or similar", "ts": "2026-05-17T21:01:58+00:00", "time": "00:01:58"}
{"type": "text", "stream": "stdout", "text": "", "ts": "2026-05-17T21:01:58+00:00", "time": "00:01:58"}
